id: ops-ab8i
title: Restore --repos routing for every fleet command
description: "The pm CLI parser drops --repos values because all seven pm-ops flag definitions declare list:true without the required string value_type, silently falling back to the current directory."
type: Issue
status: closed
priority: 1
tags[4]: "area:cli-ux","area:sdk-contract",context-management,regression
created_at: "2026-07-14T02:16:35.558Z"
updated_at: "2026-07-14T02:31:40.139Z"
closed_at: "2026-07-14T02:31:40.137Z"
author: codex-root
acceptance_criteria: All seven flag definitions satisfy the current pm SDK string-list contract; a parser-boundary regression test covers command registration; installed CLI tests prove supplied paths are used and cwd fallback is not; invalid paths remain explicit and safe; full release gate passes.
parent: ops-bfg9
reviewer: codex-root
risk: high
confidence: high
release: 2026.7.14
severity: high
environment: pm-ops 2026.7.11-1 with @unbrained/pm-cli 2026.7.13
repro_steps: "Install pm-ops into a clean pm project, run any ops subcommand with --repos pointing outside cwd, and observe the handler receives no repos option and scans cwd."
resolution: "Restored repository scope through current SDK command, schema, and parser capabilities; added installed black-box regression coverage; filed the host coercion defect as pm-cli issue #550."
expected_result: "scan, policy, verify-release, report, status, outdated, and audit all preserve comma-separated and repeated --repos values through the real pm CLI parser; missing paths produce explicit per-repository diagnostics."
actual_result: "All seven commands now declare typed repeatable repository flags and variadic additional-repository arguments. A parser compatibility bridge preserves CLI values on pm 2026.7.13 while leaving structured SDK/MCP options unchanged. Isolated install/package-doctor coverage, all CLI spellings, explicit missing paths, full 40-test real-data run, release gate, production audit, and package dry-run pass."
affected_version: 2026.7.11-1
fixed_version: 2026.7.14
component: SDK command flag parsing
regression: true
customer_impact: "Agents can receive authoritative-looking fleet results for the wrong repository, breaking project-management-as-context-management decisions."
comments[1]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-14T02:27:45.170Z",codex-root,"Black-box baseline proved pm ops status --repos <missing> exited 0 while reporting the clean fixture cwd instead. Adding value_type:string made pm contracts/help correct but the installed handler still received repos: []. Published host defect: https://github.com/unbraind/pm-cli/issues/550. Package workaround now uses the declared parser capability to recover only missing CLI --repos occurrences; structured SDK/MCP options remain authoritative and unchanged. Installed isolated tests cover all seven commands, one value, repeated values, comma lists, explicit missing-path diagnostics, and package doctor activation."
files[3]{path,scope,note}:
  index.ts,project,SDK flag metadata and repository resolution
  test/ops.test.ts,project,Parser-boundary and installed CLI regressions
  package.json,project,Current pm CLI SDK and pm-changelog pins
tests[1]{command,path,scope,timeout_seconds}:
  "npm run release:check",.,project,180
docs[1]{path,scope,note}:
  README.md,project,Public --repos usage contract
close_reason: "Verified all seven installed CLI routes, structured SDK preservation, real-repository behavior, and release readiness; upstream host defect tracked in pm-cli #550."
body: "Fleet finding mirrored from private companion item pm-cli-website-ifph. Prior partial fix/context: ops-f4vp. Public source remains isolated from hosted-service and user data. Upstream host parser defect: https://github.com/unbraind/pm-cli/issues/550."
